<TITLE> BDR man dies at Sylhet hospital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May2 (bdnews24.com)A BDR member died at Sylhet Osmani Medical College Hospital Saturday. Sepoy Renu Mia of 38 Rifle Battalion hailed from Aambari village of Sunamganj The commander of 38 Rifle Battalion, Col. Gazi Salauddin, told bdnews24.com said, "Renu Mia was admitted to Sylhet Medical College Hospital at 2pm when he felt severe pain in the chest after taking his meal." "He fell unconscious during ECG . The duty doctor declared him dead after he had been shifted to cardiac care unit," Salauddin added. The doctor at the emergency department confirmed the death. Earlier in March, the body of another border guard was recovered from Sylhet BDR headquarters. 
